Class Weapon

  • java.lang.Object
    • Item
      • Weapon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Item>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Bow, Sword

    public abstract class Weapon
extends Item
    The abstract class Weapon describes items that can be used offensively in combat. Weapons carry information about the damage they can deal, as well as their durability. If a weapon's durability reaches zero, it breaks. This class defines the abstract method polish() which a sub-class can implement in order to improve various stats of the weapon.
    Version:
    2016-09-22
    Author:
    Nicholas

    • Method Detail

      • polish

        public abstract void polish()
        "Polishing" the weapon should increase its stat modifiers by varying amounts, depending on what type the weapon is. Each time polish() is called on an instance of Weapon, stat modifiers should increase or decrease by MODIFIER_CHANGE_RATE. No more, no less.

      • use

        public java.lang.String use()
        Description copied from class: Item
        "Uses" the Item, returning a descriptive string of what happened when used.
        Specified by:
        use in class Item
        Returns:
        The text describing what happened when using the Weapon.
        See Also:
        "Using" a Weapon lowers its effective durability by Weapon.MODIFIER_CHANGE_RATE. If the effective durability of the Weapon hits or drops below 0, the Weapon will "break". If the Weapon "breaks", the method should output this information to the player, otherwise a String describing the use and damage dealt is returned.
